					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2315453#post-2849623</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2315453/scp-3792#post-2849623</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 11 Jun 2017 20:10:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Charles S5</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2993667</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;Smoke from SCP-3792 generates a number of SCP-3792-1 correlating to the amount released.&quot;</p> <p>That's pretty vague, based on what amount released does an instance of SCP-3792-1 occur? Can this be explained in depth with one additional sentence? It's not exactly an important detail, but one would expect that the Foundation would know how much smoke caused an instance of it or would say something more detailed then just &quot;correlates to amount released&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2315453#post-2849621</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2315453/scp-3792#post-2849621</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 11 Jun 2017 20:10:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The humanoids here remind me a bit of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1362">SCP-1362</a>. Maybe they are from the same dimension?</p> <p>Either way its a neat skip. Summoning smoke creatures to steal things for you is pretty great since its not like much can really keep them from getting in (unless its an airtight room?). On top of that, its nice to see the Chicago Spirit get another nod.</p> <p>+1. Good job Roget.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
